Don't usually keep one of these (git does it automatically) but want to dump a bunch of old notes here

popmap=$projhome/popmap_radsex.tsv
gen_assm=/mnt/ceph/stah3621/diorhabda/assemble_genome/carinulata_arced_scaffolds.fa

Date:Feb 19 2020
Following walk-through:
Samples are de-multiplexed individuals from GWAS core-edge cdl and flight study (phenotyped and sexed by Eliza Clark at CSU)

RadSex/bin/radsex process --input-dir sexed_samples/ --output-file coverage_table.tsv --threads 16 --min-cov 5

RadSex/bin/radsex distrib --input-file coverage_table.tsv --output-file distribution.tsv --popmap-file popmap_radsex.tsv --min-cov 5


RadSex/bin/radsex signif --input-file coverage_table.tsv --output-file significant_markers.tsv --popmap-file popmap_radsex.tsv --min-cov 5

RadSex/bin/radsex map --input-file coverage_table.tsv --output-file mapping_results.tsv --popmap-file $popmap --genome-file $gen_assm --min-cov 5

cat $gen_assm | awk '$0 ~ ">" {if (NR > 1) {print c;} c=0;printf substr($0,2,100) "\t"; } $0 !~ ">" {c+=length($0);} END { print c; }' > scaffold_lengths.txt

### Run some tests to examine the role of coverage thresholds
for m in 2 10 20 30
do
RadSex/bin/radsex process --input-dir sexed_samples/ \
--output-file coverage_table_${m}.tsv \
--threads 16 --min-cov $m

RadSex/bin/radsex distrib --input-file coverage_table_${m}.tsv \
 --output-file distribution_${m}.tsv \
--popmap-file $popmap --min-cov $m

RadSex/bin/radsex signif --input-file coverage_table_${m}.tsv \
 --output-file significant_markers_${m}.tsv \
--popmap-file $popmap --min-cov $m

RadSex/bin/radsex distrib --input-file coverage_table_${m}.tsv \
 --output-file distribution_${m}.tsv \
 --popmap-file $popmap --min-cov $m

RadSex/bin/radsex map --input-file coverage_table_${m}.tsv \
 --output-file mapping_results_${m}.tsv \
--popmap-file $popmap --genome-file $gen_assm --min-cov ${m}

done


### Pull out these loci and blast them to see if we can verify their identity
### Low cov to get male markers and high cov to get female markers
RadSex/bin/radsex subset --input-file coverage_table.tsv \
--output-file significant_markers.fa \
--popmap-file $popmap --min-cov 5 \
--min-males 60 --max-females 5 \
--output-format fasta


